# Router and Switch Configuration Project Report

## Introduction

This project demonstrates how routers and switches can be configured using Cisco Packet Tracer to enable communication between two different networks.

## Objective

The objective of this project is to understand router configuration, switch configuration, and IP addressing in a Local Area Network (LAN) environment.

## Network Devices Used

* Cisco 1841 Router
* Cisco 2960 Switch (2)
* Personal Computers (4)

## Implementation Steps

1. Created the network topology using Cisco Packet Tracer.
2. Connected PCs to switches using Ethernet cables.
3. Connected the switches to the router.
4. Assigned IP addresses to all PCs.
5. Configured router interfaces with appropriate IP addresses.
6. Configured switch hostnames.
7. Tested network connectivity using ping commands.

## Result

All devices successfully communicated with each other across two different networks.

## Conclusion

This project helped in understanding basic networking concepts such as router configuration, switch configuration, IP addressing, and communication between multiple LAN networks.
